import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=name_counts.max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common name: {name_counts.idxmax()} ({name_counts.max():.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['cx'], data['cy'], alpha=0.5)
    corr = data['cx'].corr(data['cy'])
    ax.plot(data['cx'], corr*data['cx'], color='red')
    ax.set_xlabel('cx')
    ax.set_ylabel('cy')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between cx and cy?')
    ax.legend(['Correlation line'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
